The paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) in a robotics competition, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of reward shaping and goal setting also falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Deep Q Learning (DQL), which is a subfield of Reinforcement Learning, and A* algorithm, which falls under the category of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.LG, followed by cs.SY and cs.CV.
